dict.string:
Cook agnolloti
Fry garlic and mushrooms for 2-3 min
Add beans, tomato and pepper for 2 min
Mix and serve with cheese

1. Preheat the oven to 190 degrees C. Line a 9-inch pie plate with pie dough and stick in freezer while you prepare the other quiche ingredients.
2. In a large skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add the asparagus spears, and spinach. Cook until asparagus spears are slightly tender and spinach is wilted. Transfer spinach to a colander. Press firmly with the back of a spoon to squeeze out as much liquid as possible. Set aside.
3. In a large bowl, whisk together eggs and milk. Stir in the feta and mozzarella cheese. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
4. Remove pie crust from the freezer. Place asparagus pieces, spinach, and green onions on the bottom of the crust. Pour the egg and cheese mixture over the vegetables and into the crust.
5. Bake the quiche for 45 minutes or until quiche is set and slightly golden brown. Let quiche stand for 15 minutes before serving.

1. Core the apples
2. Stuff with dried fruit mix
3. Add a few tablespoons of water over the apples
4. Bake at 180C for 30-40 mins

Remove stems from mushrooms and dice.
Mix, diced mushroom stems, chopped onion, 75g tomatoes, spinach, garlic, parsley and basil with 1 tablespoon of olive oil.
Fill the cups with mixture, top with grated cheese.
Bake at 160C for 10-15 minutes until tender.
Blend the chilli, pine nuts, vinegar, 100g tomatoes, 1 tablespoon olive oil and 1 teaspoon of basil to make the dressing.

1. Prick skin of potatoes in several places and place on kitchen paper around edge of microwave turntable. Cook potatoes uncovered , on high for about 12 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Or bake in hot oven, 200C, for about 1 hour or until tender.
2. Saute onion and garlic in oil until onion softens. Add vegetables and mushrooms and cook until tender. Stir in chopped tomatoes and bring to boil. Simmer until mixture thickens slightly.
3. Cut a cross in the top of the cooked potato and gently push to open. Spoon topping into and over potato and top with grated cheese.
Baked Potatoes With Mushroom & Vegetable Filling

## Potatoes
Bake at 220'C for 45-60min
## Salsa
Chop ingredients finely and mix well

Rinse and trim the aubergine and squash, and cut into medium thick slices. Slice the halloumi cheese into thin slices. Place the vegetables and cheese in layers. Start with a slice of aubergine, then cheese, squash, cheese, tomato and end with cheese.
Brush with a little olive oil, wrap in foil and place on the grill over medium heat for 10 minutes or until tender. Vegetables can also be placed in a casserole dish and baked in the oven at 350 F (175 C) for 30 minutes or until done.

Coat tofu in garlic, grill with tomatoes, mushrooms, asparagus and onion for 3-5 min
Remove the tofu and cut into bite sized pieces
Make dressing by mixing the oil, juice and herbs in a jar and shake
Mix to serve

- Combine all ingredients and season
- Heat pan over medium heat and spray with oil
- Place 0.25 cup of mixture and cook 3 min each side

1/ heat oil, saute onion and cap until tender
2/ add paste, mince, beans and 0.25 cups of water, heat thru
3/ serve in shells with lettuce, tomato, avocado and cheese

Fry onion, capsicum and zucchini until tender
place veg mix, beans, feta, tomato on half of tortilla, fold and cook in pan turning once or in sandwich press
Heat oil in pan, add green beans and garlic, stir-fry for 1 minute Add tomatoes, olives, kidney beans, wine, juice and honey and heat through. Stir through the feta and nuts.
Beans With Tomatoes, Feta And Olives

Preheat oven to 200C In a pot combine sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice and water. Stir to dissolve the cornstarch, add the fruit. Bring to the boil and then simmer for 1 minute. Add more sugar if required. Pour berry mixture into a baking dish.
Combine dry topping ingredients in a bowl. Melt the butter and whisk into the buttermilk. Mix the two together until just combined.
Drop the dough by spoonfuls onto the berry mixture. Bake for 20-25 minutes until the biscuit crust is golden.

Heat oil. Fry onion and capsicum 3-4 min till soft.
Add garlic, chilli for 5 min.
Add chilli powder, cumin, coriander, beans, tomatoes and stock.
Bring to boil, simmer uncovered, 40-45min.
Sprinkle chocolate over chilli, leave for 2 min. Stir.
Mix avocado, red onion, coriander, lime juice and tomato.
Serve over chilli.
Fry onion until soft. Add spices, water and beans. Simmer covered for 5 minutes. Mash a bit and continue cooking until water has evaporated. Heat tortillas. Fill tortillas.
1 Oven 190'C 2 Line dish with pastry 3 Add broccoli 4 Blend remaining ingredients (not cheese) 5 Add to broccoli, top with cheese 6 Bake 15 min, bake at 160'C for 20 min
1. Fry onion, capsicum & carrot until soft. 2. Add tomato, tomato paste, peas, corn & TVP. Cook 2-3 minutes. Stir in tins of beans. 3. Make up tortillas. 4. Bake 15-20 minutes at 180C

Heat oil, stir fry onion and garlic for 1 min
Add ginger, saute 1 min
Stir in capsicum, peas and corn, 2 min
Add remaining ingredients, 2 min
Serve with noodles

1. Heat oil in saucepan, add onion, garlic, till soft. 2. Add cauliflower, spices for 2 minutes. 3. Add tomatoes, stock and bring to the boil. 4. Reduce heat, simmer, COVERED, 10 minutes
Meanwhile
5. Cube tofu. Head oil in frying pan and cook tofu till brown.
Serve with rice.
Cauliflower, Pea And Fried Tofu Curry

1. Heat oil in a large saucepan. Add vegetables and saut. Add oregano.
2. Add tomatoes and stock. Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
3.Stir through chickpeas and risoni. Simmer a further 10 minutes.
Cook quinoa Mix lettuce and chopped avocado together Cook chickpeas with teryaki sauce Mix chickpeas and quinoa together Serve layered in a bowl

1. Heat oil, cook onion & garlic stirring until onion is soft.
2. Add spices, cook for 2 minutes.
3. Add tinned tomatoes and simmer for 5 minutes.
4. Add chickpeas and coriander.
5. Soften tortillas in the microwave.
6. Fill the tortillas with chickpea mixture, lettuce, cheese, avocado and tomato

Mix rockets, chickpeas, feta and tomatoes in a bowl
Place oil, juice, mustard and salt in a jar and shake
Mix and serve

1/ Fry onion, garlic, ginger till soft 2/ Add potatoes, curry powder and bay leaves, 2 min 3/ Add spinach, tinned tomatoes and chickpeas, simmer 15 min 4/ Add garam masala and coriander 5/ Serve with rice.
1. Heat oil 2. Garlic, sprint onions, 1 minute 3. Chilli Powder, salt, 30 seconds 4. Water, beans, bring to boil, simmer, 10 minutes 5. Buitillas, mixture, cheese, tomato, sour cream
add powders to bowl add melted cacao butter (or coconut oil) mix well pour onto a tray and put in the fridge to set

Break up chocolate and melt with half the cream in a saucepan over a low heat. Allow to cool.
Whisk egg whites with sugar till stiff.
Whisk remaining cream with vanilla till it forms firm peaks.
Fold 1/3 of egg whites into chocolate.
Fold in remaining egg whites.
Fold in cream.
Chill for 4+ hours before serving (48hrs max).

Cook noodles.
Heat oil, add onion, carrot, stirfry 1 min.
Add mushrooms, peas, cucumber, stirfry 1 min.
Add noodles, spinach, beansprouts.
Blend flour, soy sauce and add. Heat through.

1/ Cream together butter and sugar 2/ Beat in eggs and vanilla 3/ Slowly add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt 4/ Mix in choc chunks 5/ Drop dough 2" apart onto parchment-lined baking sheets 6/ Sprinkle with sea salt 7/ Bake at 180'C for 12 minutes, or until golden brown around the edges

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Quarter zucchini lengthwise, then cut crosswise into 0.25 inch think triangles. Halve and peel shallot, then thinly slice. Halve tomatoes lengthwise. Pick a few parsley leaves from stems for garnish, then finely chop the rest of the bunch.
Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and cook, tossing, until browned, 5-7 minutes. Add shallot, a pinch of chilli flakes (to taste), and a drizzle of olive oil. Cook, tossing, until shallot is softened, 2-3 minutes.
Once water is boiling, add ravioli to pot. Cook until tender and floating to the top, about 4 minutes. Carefully scoop out and reserve 0.5 cup pasta water then drain.
Once shallot is softened, stir tomatoes into pan, then reduce heat to low. Stir in sour cream, half the Parmesan, stock and 0.25 cup pasta cooking water. Season with salt, pepper, chopped parsley, and more chilli flakes (to taste).
Add ravioli to pan, increase heat to medium, and gently toss to coat ravioli in sauce. Cook until sauce thickens slightly, 1-2 minutes. TIP: Add more pasta cooking water, if needed, to give sauce a loose consistency.
Divide ravioli mixture between plates, then garnish with remaining Parmesan and reserved parsley leaves and serve.

1. Fry onion, capsicum & zucchini in oil until tender.
2. For each of the 4 tortillas: Put 0.25 of veg mix, 0.25 beans, scatter some cubed feta and diced tomato on half a tortilla.
3. Fold tortilla over filling. Cook on med heat, turn once.
4. Make salsa with 1 tomato and avocado. Serve salsa on side.
Crispy Mexican Bean And Veg Tortillas

1.Heat 2 teaspoons oil in a non-stick frying pan. Cook onion over medium-high heat for 3 minutes until tender. Stir curry paste and cumin. Cook for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Cool for 5 minutes.
2. Mash chickpeas in a large bowl. Add onion mixture, egg, coriander, carrot and breadcrumbs. Stir to combine. Divide mixture into 8 portions and mould each portion into a patty. Lightly coat in chickpea flour and shake off excess.
3. Heat remaining oil in a large non-stick frying pan. Cook the patties over medium heat for 4-5 minutes per side, or until golden brown and cooked through.
4. Place lettuce and tomato on each roll base. Top with two patties, then remaining bread and serve with mango chutney.

Process chickpeas and onion in FP
Add remaining items except oil, shape
Heat oil, cook till brown
Serve with lebanese salad in pita breads with egg and cheese

Heat oil in a wok over medium heat. Add 2.5cm cubes of tofu.
Fry for 2-3 minutes or until golden.
Add onion, garlic, fry 1 min
Add ginger, chilli, fry 1 min
Add beans, corn, capsicum, fry 2 min
Add sprouts, spinach, sauces, fry 2-3 min
Serve with noodles

1. Blend the berries on low.
2. Mix even quantities of yoghurt and berries in a bowl.
3. Leave in fridge for 2 hours.
4. Pour into freezer bowl and churn for 30-40 min.

1/ Cook the pasta according to the package directions; drain, rinse, drain again, and set aside in a large bowl. Cover to keep warm.
2/ Meanwhile, coat a large nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Add the broccoli, mushrooms, onion, and bell pepper; cook over medium-high heat for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring often. Add the broth, basil, thyme, crushed red pepper, and salt; mix until well combined. Bring to a boil and cook for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
3/ Reduce the heat to low then stir in the sour cream and continue stirring until heated through. Pour over the pasta; toss and serve immediately.

1. Peel, quarter and core apples
2. Combine softened butter and sugar. Beat until thick and creamy.
3. Add lightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
4. Sift flour and baking powder and mix in a quarter at a time. Add milk.
5. Transfer to 23cm round cake tin, lined with paper. Smooth the top.
6. Slice apples 3/4 through and press deep into batter, make 2 layers of apples.
7. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon
8. Bake at 180C for 50 mins. If apples are firm, cover with foil and cook for 10 min.
9. Cool, dust with icing sugar.

Saute onion, garlic, carrots, zucchini in oil for 5 min or till soft
Still in paprika, nutmeg, parsley and tomato paste
Add rest and cook over low heat for 10 min
Serve with cooked rice

Boil the two lentils, ginger, tumeric, garlic in 2.5 cups of water for 15-20 until soft
Cook pasta
Heat oil, stir fry onion, garlic, chilli and vegetables for 10 min
Add pasta and lentils and oregano
Combine all salad ingredients in a large bowl. Add Oregano Lemon Vinaigrette ingredients to a bowl or mason jar then whisk or shake to combine. Pour over salad then toss to combine and serve.

Cook quinoa. Cool.
Combine everything.
For dressing whisk together oil, vinegar and oregano.

1. Crack eggs into a bowl, whisk to combine. Heat lightly oiled pan over low heat and pour in egg mixture. Wait for egg to set, then gently roll egg onto itself. Remove from pan and slice egg roll thinly - set aside.
2. Heat sesame oil in pan and add garlic,onion, carrots, corn and mushrooms, cook for 2 minutes. Add capsicums and peas and stir-fry vegetables until just cooked.
3. Mix soy sauce and chilli sauce together and then sitr through rice mixture. Serve topped with sliced egg roll.

1. Fry onion in oil until s oft.
2. Add everything except the vegies & beans, simmer for 15 minutes
3. Add vegies and beans and heat through

Cook pasta.
Fry garlic, add remaining ingredients and stir until spinach is wilted and beans are warmed through
Serve topped with grated cheese

Cover burghul with boiling water and stand for 10 min
Combine burghul, chickpeas, chopped tomatoes, parsley, lemon juice and pepper
Combine hummus, yoghurt, chilli and cumin.
1. Place lentils, rice and stock in a pan and simmer for 20 minutes. 2. Add everything else except the salt & pepper 3. Bring to the boil and simmer for 10-15 minutes 4. Season with salt & pepper

Heat a large pot over medium-high heat.
When hot, add onion and bell pepper; cook, stirring frequently, until vegetables brown and begin to stick to the bottom of the pot, about 6 minutes.
Stir in 3 tablespoons of the broth and continue to cook, stirring, until onion is soft and lightly browned.
Stir in garlic and chili powder and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add lentils, tomatoes and remaining broth. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, partially covered, 30 minutes or until lentils are almost tender.
Uncover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Stir in cilantro and serve.

Preheat oven to 190'C
1. Boil lentils in large pan of water, uncovered, for 15 min. 2. Heat oil in pan, add garlic, onion till soft. 3. Add capsicum, mushroom, zucchini and spices, cook till tender. 4. Still in lentils. 5. Layer mixture, ricotta and pasta into greased dish. 6. Bake for 45 min. 7. Sprinkle with breadcrumbs, parsley and edam.

1. Heat pan, add oil, celery, capsicum, onion and garlic for 7 minutes.
2. Add bay leaf and thyme, cook for 2 minutes.
3. Add stock and bring to the boil.
4. Add zucchini, tomatoes and corn. Simmer for 5 minutes and then add the rice.
5. Add salt, pepper and chilli. Bring to the boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
6. Add the red kidney beans and parsley, cook for 5 minutes.
1. Chill glasses with ice cubes 2. Add all ingredients to shaker 3. Shake for 30 seconds 4. Strain and serve

Preheat oven to 232'C Bring medium pot to boil Half tomatoes then chop Half, peel and thinly slice shallot Stir together vinegar and 0.5tsp sugar in a medium bowl, add shallot and tomatoes, toss to coat Boil orzo for 6-8 minutes and drain Drain, rinse and pat drive chickpeas. Place on baking sheet, drizzle with olive oil, spice, 0.5 tsp paprika, salt and pepper. Roast for 8-10 minutes Chop mint leaves roughly. Stir with orzo and olive oil In a small bowl stir together sour cream, half the feta, 0.25 tsp paprika, 1 Tbsp water Once chickpeas are done stir into orzo Add rocket leave with drizzle of olive oil to shallot and tomato mixture and toss to coat To serve, layer orzo, rocket mixture, feta and dressing

Heat oil in a saucepan and saute onion, capsicum & courgette until soft.
Add mushrooms and saut for 1 minute.
Stir through pasta sauce, butter beans, basil & salt. Heat through.
Pour mixture into a large casserole dish. Cut eggplant into 1cm slices. Brush eggplant with extra oil and grill until golden on both sides. Arrange eggplant over bean mixture. Sprinkle with combined crumble.
Bake in a moderate oven 180C for 30 minutes or until crumble is crisp.
Mash the avocado with the lemon juice, yoghurt and sweet chilli sauce. Spread on the tortillas Fill each tortilla with beans, chopped tomato, grated cheese and sprouts. Roll

Saute onion and garlic for 2 min
Add tofu and cook for 2-3 min till brown
Add beans, stir in juice, spices and stock
Simmer for 5-7 min
Sprinkle with seeds

1. Fry the spring onions in oil until soft.
2. Lightly beat the eggs with the herbs, salt & pepper.
3. Pour the eggs over the onions to make an omellete. Slice when cooked.
4. Heat oil in pan, add garlic & tumeric then stir in rice and lentils.
5. Add stock, tinned tomatoes & cinnamon stick. Add salt & pepper. Bring to the boil. Simmer covered for 20 min.
6. Stir in the tin of beans. Leave for 2-3 min.
7. Remove the cinnamon stick. Mix the egg slices into the rice mixture.

1. Heat oil and stir fry the onion, capsicum and garlic until soft
2. Add remaining ingredients and heat through.
3. Serve over corn chips or baked potatoes

1. Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into a mixing bowl and mix in rolled oats.
2. Make a well in the centre of dry ingredients. Mix egg, milk and margarine together. Pour into well and stir gently to combine ingredients.
3. Place of a cup of mixture in a moderately hot non-stick frypan. Cook until bubbles form, then turn and cook for a further 1-2 minutes.
4.Serve with maple syrup and fruit.
Tips Turn this into a tasty nutritious dessert by changing the topping e.g. Blueberries and yoghurt.

Break eggs into a jug, add milk, lightly mix with whisk
Dice tomato, capsicum and mushrooms
Heat a non-stick large pan to medium, spray with oil
Fry the capsicum and mushrooms till soft, remove
Add egg to pan, cook low-medium until mostly set, regularly run spatula around edge of egg
When mostly set run spatula under whole egg to ensure it is not stuck
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over half the omelette
Fold empty half of omelette over filling, let set for about a minute and then serve

1. In a pot, heat the oil and saut onion until translucent. Add carrots and garlic and saut for 1 more minute. 2. Add chopped tomatoes, lentils, tomato puree, sugar, spices and about 3 cups broth. Bring to boil and cook for about 30 minutes. 3. Boil spaghetti separately 4. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese (optional).

1. Mix rocket and spinach leaves, half the mint, orange slices and sliced red onion.
2. Scatter with olives, drizzle with dressing
3. Top with crumbled feta and remaining mint

Make the dressing: combine vinegar, garlic, basil, salt/pepper in a bowl. Slowly add olive oil, whisking to combine.
Cook orzo in salted water according to package instructions.
Meanwhile, halve tomatoes, slice green onions, and roughly chop spinach. Place in a large bowl.
Drain orzo and immediately add to large bowl. Toss. The heat from the orzo will lightly wilt the spinach.
Pour the dressing on top, toss to combine. Add feta and lightly toss.
Can eat immediately, or refrigerate for 1-2 hours and serve cold.
Orzo Salad With Spinach, Tomato, Feta

Cook noodles
Cut tofu into 2cm cubes, brown in oil
Add garlic, ginger, sambal oelek and lemon grass till fragrant
Add carrot and zuchini, cook till tender
Add egg, stir till set
Add sauces, bring to boil
Add sprouts, coriander, peanuts and noodles

1. To make the dressing, combine the olive oil, lemon juice and zest, honey and garlic in a screw top jar. Shake and season to taste.
2. Cook the orzo according to packet directions. Drain and rinse.
3. Heat a dash of oil in a frying pan over medium heat. Cook haloumi for 1 minute on each side or until it is golden brown. Remove from the pan and set aside.
4. Place the drained Wattie's Lentils in a large bowl with the drained orzo, onion, cucumber, tomatoes, mint, parsley, olives and haloumi.
5. Add the dressing and toss gently to combine.

Fry onion, garlic and celery until soft.
Add chickpeas and tomatoes.
Cover, simmer, 15min.
Cook pasta.
Mix.

- Combine oil, vinegar and garlic
- Add pasta, spinach, olives, capers and cheese
- Toss well
Penne With Spinach, Feta And Olives
Spread the pizza bases with tomato paste. Place chopped toppings on top, finish with beans and cheese. Bake at 240C for 10 minutes

Preheat over to 240'C
1. Microwave pumpkin, potato. 2. Combine pumpkin, potato, spinach, feta, edam and egg in a bowl. 3. Add to greased pan, top with onion. 4. Bake for 25min.
Serve with salad.

1. Cook rice noodles according to package (most you soak in hot water for 6-8 minutes). Then rinse under cold water and set aside.
2. Chop all vegetables and set aside.
3. In a large, wide bowl, fill halfway with warm water. Place a clean towel onto a flat surface next to the water bowl and make sure all of your cut vegetables and rice noodles are within reach.
4. Take a piece of rice paper, dunk it into the warm water and let it soak for about 30-40 seconds, until it softens. Be sure not to leave it for too long or else it will become too thin and rip.
5. Once soft, carefully lay the rice paper onto the towel and place about 2-4 pieces of each ingredient in a bundle on one end of the rice paper.
6. Fold the rice paper closest to the ingredients overtop.
7. Then fold the two opposite sides over the center (like a burrito).
8. Finally tightly roll down the remainder of the paper until it is fully sealed.
9. Put your sauce into small serving dishes and serve altogether.

Place rice and milk in a pan. Bring to the boil.
Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is soft and most of the liquid has been absorbed
Remove from heat, stir in sugar and leave to stand for 5 minutes.
Serve with berries

Preheat oven to 200C. Thickly slice courgettes. De-seed and cut the capsicum into 1cm pieces, cut the onion into wedges. Cut eggplant into 1cm pieces. Place in a roasting tray and toss through 2 Tbsp of olive oil. Roast for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
While vegetables are roasting cook the quinoa. Add to a pot of lightly salted boiling water and cook for 8-9 minutes. Drain and rinse through cold water. Drain thoroughly. Put into a large bowl.
Toss - cup Eta Lite & Free French Dressing through the roasted vegetables while they are still warm. Cool. Add to cooked quinoa and carefully mix through adding a liitle more dressing if wished. Transfer to a serving platter. Garnish with fresh basil leaves.

Preheat oven to 190C.
Place vegetables on roasting tray, brush with olive oil and bake in oven, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until tender.
Line a rectangular flan tin with the pastry. Press pastry into corners and then trim overhanging pastry. Prick the base and bake blind for about 10 minutes.
Add vegetables to the pastry base, crumble feta over the top and bake for a further 10 minutes, or until pastry is lightly browned.

1. Combine, rocket, sliced pears, half the chopped hazelnuts and half the parmesan in a bowl.
2. Drizzle with Praise all natural apple & honey dressing
3. Top with remaining hazelnuts and parmesan

1. Cook noodles as per instructions on packet without flavouring. 2. Heat oil in frypan and cook soy fillets until golden on both sides. Remove from heat and slice. Add onion, capsicum and saute until soft. Stir through beans and saute for 1 minute. 3. Add satay sauce, soy fillets, drained noodles and heat through.
Toast the english muffins Poach the eggs Assemble the schmuffin

1. Cut potatoes into 1.5 cm cubes. Place in a large pan with salt, cover with water. Bring to the boil, cool uncovered for 3 min. Remove from heat, cover and stand for 8 min. Drain well.
2. Fry chopped onion and garlic in oil for 8 min. Add the potatoes and cook for 5 min.
3. Beat the eggs with the parsley.
4. Mix the eggs and vegetables together, pour into a frying pan and cook on low, covered for 10 min. Brown the top under the grill if desired.

Heat oil, add spring onions, tofu and capsicum, saute 5 min
Add paste, sprouts, peas and corn, stir fry 2 min
Add cooked rice
Add sauce

1. Oven to 180'C.
2. Microwave spinach. Add nutmeg, salt, pepper.
3. Oil pan. Sweat onion till soft. Add the garlic, tomatoes, bay leaf, a few basil leaves and lemon zest and gently simmer for 20 minutes until thickened. Season with salt and pepper.
3. Stir in the ricotta, beaten egg and parmesan into spinach. Season to taste.
4. Pipe the mixture into the cannelloni tubes and lay them in a 20cm x 25cm oven dish.
5. Spread the tomato sauce over the cannelloni. Scatter over most of the basil, lay the mozzarella slices on top, drizzle with extra-virgin olive oil and season.
6. Bake for 3540 minutes or till the top is golden and the pasta tender
NOTE: If the top browns too fast, cover the dish with foil.
7. Remove from the oven and let stand for a few minutes before serving with the remaining basil.

Combine spinach, feta, ricotta, egg, spinach and sauted onion.
Bake 200C for 25-30 minutes.

Heat oil, add onion, garlic, chilli and mushrooms and cook until soft
Stir in tomatoes, paste, wine, olives and basil
Simmer covered for 20 min until thick
Add spinach and simmer uncovered till warm
Add pasta and cheese

1. Heat the oil in a pan, and cook the red onion and garlic over a medium heat for a few minutes until transparent.
2. Add the spinach, and cook for a further 1-2 minutes until wilted. Remove from the heat and leave to cool for a couple of minutes.
3. Add the drained chickpeas, ricotta cheese and the egg, and mix well. Season with a pinch of nutmeg and a generous amount of salt and pepper.
4. Heat the oven to 190C (Gas Mark 5 / 375F).
5. Lay one sheet of filo on a lightly greased baking sheet, and give it a couple of sprays of oil. Add another sheet, spray again, and add a third sheet (you could use more than 3 if you like, but I think 3 works pretty well).
6. Spoon your filling onto the pastry - since I made a large rectangular pie, I covered the whole sheet, just leaving an inch or so around each side. Spread the filling out into an even layer. Top with three more sheets of pastry, again spraying lightly with oil between each layer.
7. Scrunch the excess pastry around each edge to seal the pie - I just loosely tucked it underneath. Make a couple of small slits in the top, and bake for around 40 minutes, until the pastry is golden brown.
Spinach And Ricotta Strudel With Chickpeas

Wash the spinach and put it in a large saucepan with just the water that clings to its leaves. Heat for 1-2 mins until gently wilted, then tip into a colander and allow to cool. Once cool, squeeze out the excess water and chop finely.
Heat the oil in a frying pan and gently cook the onion for about 5 mins until softened. Stir in the garlic and chilli flakes, and cook for 1 min more. Tip into a bowl, add the spinach, courgettes, rice and cheese, and toss together.
Beat the 2 large eggs with the mustard, a pinch of salt and a good grinding of black pepper. Add to the spinach mixture and mix well. Heat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6. Put a baking sheet in the oven to preheat. Cut the pastry in half and roll 1 piece out on a lightly floured work surface until you have a sheet that measures 32 x 17cm. Place in a 30 x 15cm tin and prick it well all over the base. Roll out the remaining piece of pastry to the same size.
Spoon the spinach mixture into the pastry base. Beat together the milk and remaining medium egg, then brush the edges of the pastry with it. Lay the other sheet of pastry over the top and press down gently to seal. Brush the top with a little more beaten egg and sprinkle with the sesame seeds.
Place the tin on the preheated baking tray and bake for 10 mins, then reduce the temperature to 160C/140C fan/gas 4 and bake for a further 30 mins until the pastry is golden. Leave to cool for 10 mins before cutting into squares.

- Cook pasta, drain
- In pan, cook ginger, garlic in oil for 15 sec. Stir in broccoli, mushrooms and sauce. Cook 5 min.
- Toss with pasta and onions.

Cook rice
Heat the oil in a large pan (one with high sides) or wok over medium-high heat and add the tofu, turning to brown on all sides.
Lower the heat to medium and add the garlic and curry paste.
Cook, stirring, for about a minute.
Add the peppers and cook until slightly softened.
Pour in the coconut milk and soy sauce; stir to incorporate the curry paste.
Add the peas and simmer for 10-15 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in the lime juice, cilantro and green onion.
Fry tofu slabs on medium heat for 4 mins each side. Onion goes in at the same time as the tofu.
1 large Roasted sweet potato cubed, oiled, seasoned, bake 400F 20 min then 10 min.

1/ Cook Penne
2/ Saute zucchini, add beans, boil 2 minutes
3/ Add and wilt spinach
4/ Stir in pasta

Cook onion, celery, carrot and garlic. Cover,cook low heat, 8-10min.
Stir in chilli powder and cumin, add tomatoes, stock, thyme and bay leaf.
Cook 15min uncovered.
Add cauliflower, zuchini and corn. Cover, cook 15min.
Add beans, cook 10min uncovered.
Serve with rice.
Chop the vegetables and tofu. Marinate the tofu in bbq or satay sauce. Thread the skewers with the mixture of tofu and veg. Grill, turning until browned

1. Saute onion in oil until soft. Add mushrooms, courgette and carrot and cook until soft.
2. Mix cottage cheese, rice and eggs in a bowl and add vegetables.
3. Press 1 tablespoon of mix into patties and roll in breadcrumbs. Heat a little oil in pan and cook patties on each side until golden brown.

Heat oil, add garlic, ginger and onions, stirfry for 1 min
Add broccoli, capsicum, mushrooms and olives, stirfry for 2 min
Add sauces, sprinkle with seeds

Cook Rice.
Mix rice, coriander, juice.
Sautee onion, garlic.
Add beans, rice, chili, cumin.
Warm.
Serve with scrambled egg, avocado, sour cream, olives, cheese and/or hot sauce.

1/ Fry onion, carrot, garlic till tender 2/ Add capsicums, celery and chilli powder, cook 6 min till tender 3/ Add mushrooms, cook 4 min 4/ Add tomatoes, kidney beans and corn, oregano, basil, cumin 5/ Bring to boil, cover, simmer, 20 mins

1. Mix carrots, oregano, and spaghetti sauce together.
2. Mix Ricotta, spinach, and eggs together in separate bowl.
3. Spread cup spaghetti sauce in bottom of 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
4. Layer 3 lasagna noodles, remaining sauce, Ricotta mixture, sliced zucchini, sliced mushrooms, Mozzarella, and Parmesan.
5. Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
6. Bake in 180'C degrees oven for about 45 minutes.

Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium-high heat.
Once oil is hot add onion and saute until tender, about 4 minutes, adding in garlic during last 30 seconds of sauteing.
Add in tinned tomatoes, cooked quinoa, stock (start with 1 1/2 cups then add more later if desired), chili powder, cumin, paprika, coriander, cayenne pepper and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bring mixture just to a boil, then reduce heat to a simmer, cover pot and allow to simmer 30 minutes.
Add in all beans, corn, coriander and lime and cook until heated through.

Grater zucchini, dice onion
Combine zucchini, onion, sifted flour, oil, cheese and lightly beaten eggs. Season with salt and pepper
Pour into well greased lamington tin, bake at 180'C for 30-40 min
